      "description": "Speaker laid before the House Subsequently, under suspension of the rules and WITHOUT REFERENCE to a Committee, the Bill was READ ONCE . Speaker FECTEAU of Biddeford MOVED to SUSPEND the rules for the purpose of giving the Bill its second reading without reference to any Committee Representative COLLAMORE of Pittsfield OBJECTED . Representative FAULKINGHAM of Winter Harbor REQUESTED a division on suspension of Joint Rule 308. The Chair ordered a division. A vote of the House was taken. 69 voted in favor of the same and 63 against, and accordingly the rules were SUSPENDED and the Bill was given its SECOND READING without REFERENCE to the Committee on Bills in the Second Reading . Motion of Representative FREDETTE of Newport to INDEFINITELY POSTPONE the Bill and accompanying papers FAILED . ROLL CALL NO. 119 (Yeas 55 - Nays 85 - Absent 10 - Excused 0 - Restricted - 1) Subsequently, the Bill was PASSED TO BE ENGROSSED . Sent for concurrence. ORDERED SENT FORTHWITH."
